{"detail":{"ID":107,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-12-29 12:23:17","post_date_gmt":"2016-12-29 12:23:17","post_content":"Obra\u2019s <em>Freedom Park<\/em> complex includes museum, memorial, <em>Garden of Remembrance<\/em> with outdoor gathering space, and administration on a 52-hectare site. As visitors ascend a spiral path, the <em>Witness Memorial<\/em> and <em>Freedom Museum<\/em> are gradually revealed in constantly shifting perspectives. Inspired by the African tradition of carving the graves of important community members from a Baobab trunk, the womb-like memorial and museum echo hollowed-out tree trunks. The memorial, a single \u201ctrunk\u201d set in a clearing of indigenous Sugarbush trees, honors apartheid victims. The Museum is configured as four soaring \u201ctrunks\u201d containing ten gallery spaces that can be traversed in sequence as if fused into one, just as trees in close proximity grow into one.","post_title":"<p>Freedom Park Memorial and Museum, Pretoria, SA 2002<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"freedom-park-memorial-and-museum-pretoria-sa-2002-2","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2017-05-16 21:35:04","post_modified_gmt":"2017-05-16 21:35:04","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=107","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw","ancestors":[],"page_template":"","post_category":[],"tags_input":[],"extended":{"year":"","images":[{"image":{"width":1500,"height":927,"file":"2016\/12\/OBRA_FREEDOM_PARK_01.jpg","sizes":{"thumbnail":{"file":"OBRA_FREEDOM_PARK_01-760x460.jpg","width":760,"height":460,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg"},"medium":{"file":"OBRA_FREEDOM_PARK_01-300x185.jpg","width":300,"height":185,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg"},"medium_large":{"file":"OBRA_FREEDOM_PARK_01-768x475.jpg","width":768,"height":475,"mime-type":"ima